Source: @PACKAGE_NAME@
Section: java
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Docker Hardened Images <dhi@docker.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13)
Standards-Version: 4.7.0
Homepage: https://aws.amazon.com/corretto/

Package: @PACKAGE_NAME@
Architecture: any
# Runtime deps for the prebuilt Corretto JVM, mapped to Debian trixie package
# names. Hardcoded because dh_shlibdeps is skipped for the prebuilt binaries.
Depends:
 ${misc:Depends},
 ca-certificates,
 tzdata,
 libc6,
 libgcc-s1,
 libstdc++6,
 libasound2t64
Description: Amazon Corretto JDK @JAVA_MAJOR_VERSION@
 Amazon Corretto is a no-cost, production-ready distribution of the OpenJDK.
 This package provides the Corretto JDK for the @JAVA_MAJOR_VERSION@ release
 line, installed under /usr/lib/jvm/@JAVA_DST_BASENAME@ with the runtime tools
 exposed on PATH via /usr/bin.

Package: @PACKAGE_NAME@-oci-config
Architecture: all
Depends: @PACKAGE_NAME@ (= ${binary:Version}), ${misc:Depends}
Description: OCI configuration for @PACKAGE_NAME@
 OCI container configuration (JAVA_HOME and JAVA_VERSION environment
 variables) for the @PACKAGE_NAME@ package.

Package: @PACKAGE_NAME@-fips
# Arch-specific: ships the native (aws-lc) ACCP jar for this architecture, so it
# must NOT be Architecture: all (that breaks the multi-arch publish — the amd64
# and arm64 builds would produce different content under one name).
Architecture: any
Depends: @PACKAGE_NAME@ (= ${binary:Version}), ${misc:Depends}
Description: FIPS 140 configuration for @PACKAGE_NAME@
 The AmazonCorrettoCryptoProvider (ACCP) FIPS provider JARs and the ACCP
 java.security overlay for @PACKAGE_NAME@, installed under /opt/aws-lc.

Package: @PACKAGE_NAME@-fips-oci-config
Architecture: all
Depends: @PACKAGE_NAME@-fips (= ${binary:Version}), ${misc:Depends}
Description: OCI FIPS configuration for @PACKAGE_NAME@
 OCI container configuration enabling FIPS mode (ACCP module path and
 java.security overlay) for @PACKAGE_NAME@.
